Peru Infrastructure Spending to Offset Slowdown, Castilla Says

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-10-19T23:14:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/peru-infrastructure-spending-to-offset-slowdown-castilla-says.html
Peru will offset a global economic
slowdown by creating thousands of jobs through public spending
on small-scale infrastructure projects, Finance Minister Miguel
Castilla said.  Peru expects to post a 1.5 percent fiscal surplus this
year, Castilla told reporters today in  Lima .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Emery in Lima at 
